entry.title: [omnibox][rich-autocompletion] Refactor omnibox selections.
entry.content:
In preparation for crrev.com/c/4596427, this CL some mostly

no-user-change refactors to clean up the selection code.



Bug fix 1: https://screenshot.googleplex.com/9qrikUSbKZq9TiR

Bug fix 2: https://screenshot.googleplex.com/Yy9CzpuRXYUeKhf



Specifically:

- Before, up/down arrow and page up/down keys were handled very

similarly but with their independent implementations. Now, they share

the same implementation. This a) reduces duplicate code, and b) fixes

a bug where page-up would not revert temporary text (see 1st

screenshot).

- Updates up/down arrows to use `StepPopupSelection()` instead of

`SetPopupSelection()`. This a) is consistent with tab traversal, b)

reduces redundant code, and c) fixes a bug where arrowing-up out of

keyword mode would leave the user in a hybrid/invalid keyword state

(see 2nd screenshot).

- Initializes `saved_temporary_selection_` to an empty selection instead

of an invalid selection. This fixes a local `DCHECK` crash with zero

input suggestions.

- Removes unused `OmniboxPopupViewViews::UnselectButton()`

- Adds comments & `DCHECK` messages. The `DCHECK` triggered once locally

but I didn't figure out why, so the extra message might be helpful in

case it triggers again.

- Makes `OmniboxEditModel::MaybeStartQueryForPopup()` private. Also

flattens its `if` branching.

- Makes `OmniboxEditModel::StepPopupSelection()` return `void`. It's

return value was never used, and it was returning an easily accessible

member variable anyways.

- Inlines a lambda that was only called immediately after it was defined

in `OmniboxPopupSelection::GetAllAvailableSelectionsSorted()`.

entry.title: [Test Automation] Improve timeout messages in Kombucha tests for LUCI
entry.content:
This CL makes several backwards-compatible changes to existing systems

in order to front the error message for a Kombucha test that times out:

- Can now override RunLoop timeout error message without also

overriding the current RunLoop timeout.

- Can generate InteractionSequence error reports via a public API.

- InteractiveTestApi now overrides the RunLoop timeout error message

and generates a failure report of new type "kSequenceTimedOut".



The net effect is that, if a Kombucha test times out, an appropriate

Kombucha error message (with step number, description, ElementID, etc.)

is printed as part of the initial timeout error message and call stack,

making the errors much easier for LUCI to parse.

entry.title: [omnibox][shortcut] Try out new feature/param setup 🤪.
entry.content:
Currently, we declare and define features in omnibox_features.h|cc. And

we declare and define params in omnibox_field_trial.h|cc. Our current

setup has a few pain points:



- Features and params are in 2 pairs of .h|.cc.

- Reading finch params 100's of times per keystroke has measurable

latency regressions. These are not fun to discover after already

starting experiments.

- Caching params is done inconsistently between features. E.g. some are

cached with provider class members. Some are cached in static local

vars where they're used. Some are cached in getter functions. Some are

cached in large structs. These all have disadvatages: messy, hard to

access in multiple places, really hard to test around, and verbose

boilerplate.



We've been kind of steering in the direction of using structs

encapsulating the feature and its params, caching their values, and

allowing some mechanism to reset their values for tests. This has worked

well for rich autocompletion, journeys, & ml scoring. But even those 3,

though they use the same general approach, each have their own unique

solution.



This CL tries to standardize this struct approach, giving free,

test-friendly, standardized caching for all features that use the

approach.



The comment in omnibox_feature_configs.h has a 1-2-3

instruction/example. And this CL migrates shortcut boosting to this new

approach as a guinna pig.

entry.title: Replace FALLBACK_REVISION with OVERRIDE_CLANG_REVISION
entry.content:
If set, the OVERRIDE_CLANG_REVISION replaces CLANG_REVISION from

//tools/clang/scripts/update.py. To keep things simple, it is used

unconditionally, so for both building and downloading Rust

packages.



So then upload_revision.py clears the OVERRIDE_CLANG_REVISION so

that rolling Rust will build it against the current Clang, if you

didn't --skip-clang.



If Rust can't be rolled, the revision change in update_rust.py should

be undone, and the OVERRIDE_CLANG_REVISION set to the value which

Rust was built against.



This avoids us suddenly jumping to an old fallback Rust revision

when the Clang package revision changes.

entry.title: Fix unnecessary AX tree traversals to prevent freezing on certain HTML
entry.content:
Previously, GetSpellingAndGrammarAttributes() looped through all

the text children of a native text field to find the spelling/grammar

information we needed to expose to assistive tech. However, we didn't

check that the text field was nonempty to start with. If it's an empty

text field, NextTextOnlyObject() will not find a descendant text node

but instead return a text node outside the text field, which can start

unnecessary tree traversals.



Now, we will only execute the above logic if the text field is nonempty.

This should guarantee that our loop traverses among only descendants

of the text field.

entry.title: [WebAuthn][CredMan] Index WebAuthnCredManDelegate by frame
entry.content:
Currently WebAuthnCredManDelegate is attached to a WebContents by

way of its UserData.



This is a problem because it is possible for multiple frames within a

single WebContents to be invoking conditional UI. This means callbacks

from the conditional requests in each frame could contend with each

other, and also a tap on a username field that activates the

conditional request could end up triggering a request associated with

the wrong frame.



This change adds a factory class that creates WebAuthnCredManDelegate

instances. The factory is WebContents bound but internally it keeps

a map of frames to delegate instances.

cookie without the `Domain` attribute using a url with an empty leading

entry.title: Reland "Extend period identified as printing content analysis"
entry.content:
This is a reland of commit 044be5b5ac3c050fb14713f634a22cb5de5171f2



Wrapped analyzing_content_ variable and access method with the

ENABLE_PRINT_CONTENT_ANALYSIS build flag.



Original change's description:

> Extend period identified as printing content analysis

>

> PrintViewManagerBase and PrintViewManager use a state variable to know

> when the document is being checked for content analysis. This state

> has been set only around the time when a snapshot is being collected,

> but has not been including the time for the actual composition and

> analysis. This interfered with the out-of-process print drivers

> feature logic, resulting in crashes when both features are being used

> because a Print Backend service client would unregister prematurely.

>

> Modify the content analysis state to track the entire time that the

> document is being checked, resetting it only once an accept/reject

> decision has been made. Update the name of this state variable to

> better reflect this new approach. This allows PrintViewManagerBase to

> check the state in some extra places and ensure that Print Backend

> client registration persists while content analysis is still in

> progress.

>

> Also add some extra detail to the logging statement in

> PrintBackendServiceManager::RegisterClient(), which was helpful to

> understand how this problem was occurring.

>

> This allows content analysis browser tests to now complete the printing

> sequence without crashing for both in-browser and OOPPD configurations.

>
